    "description": "Spot — Boston Dynamics' commercial quadruped (~32 kg, 1.1 m body length, ~110 cm tall standing). Boston Dynamics ships a publicly-available URDF for ROS / RViz integration even though Spot's actual control software is closed-source. This descriptor mirrors the public URDF's geometry; its purpose in OpenLoco is to make Spot's *kinematic shape* available as a UDD so users can simulate Spot-class designs in MuJoCo, generate ROS-compatible URDFs, and iterate on Spot-derivative custom hardware. All actuator dynamics are placeholder Tier 2 — the real Spot motors are proprietary and undocumented. Three-DoF leg per corner with hip_roll → hip_pitch → knee_pitch terminating in a fixed foot.",
    "generator": "openloco-cli"
  },
